<!--start left column-->
<div class="g12">
<div class="white_box_shadow">
<p>Cruising has never been more popular and we're delighted introduce this cruise around Croatia to our programme. The coastline around Croatia is truly spectacular with hundreds of tiny islands, some uninhabited; hidden coves; lively harbours and clear, blue seas. The best way to explore this beautiful part of the world is on small ships that can take you to places the big cruise liners could not possibly reach. These cruises are relaxed and informal affairs. The cabins are simply furnished but each has its own shower &amp; w.c. and airconditioning. Both ships have large sun decks where you can work on your tan but there are shaded areas where you can relax with a good book and a cool drink. Meals are very informal. The cruise price includes breakfast and lunch prepared by the on board cook. In the evenings, you're free to explore the harbour and find that little fish restaurant! Every day you'll sail to a different island, swim in another bay and in the evening moor up in a different port. No two days will be the same. We can't think of a more relaxing way to enjoy this beautiful part of the world.</p>
</div>
<div> </div>
<div class="white_box_shadow">
<h2>Itinerary</h2>
<p> </p>
<p><strong>Wednesday - Friday</strong>  At leisure in Opatija. Spend 3 nights in your choice of the Hotel Agava or Hotel Grand   on half board.</p>
<p><strong>Saturday  </strong><strong>Opatija - Krk</strong>   Depart from Opatija harbour at approx 13:00 for the island of Krk - the largest of the islands. There is plenty of time to explore the town of Krk. Overnight</p>
<p><strong>Sunday:</strong> <strong>Krk - Rab </strong> Sail after breakfast to Rab, known as the 'Island of Love'. Overnight in the harbour which is encircled by medieval walls.</p>
<p><strong>Monday  Rab - Zadar  </strong>After breakfast we cruise from Rab past the islands of Pag and Maun and continue to towards Zadar, for centuries the capital of Dalmatia. Short sightseeing tour included. Overnight.</p>
<p><strong>Tuesday  Zadar - Molat or Olib</strong>  An early sailing for either Molat or Olib (depending on available space in the small harbours). Overnight</p>
<p><strong>Wednesday  Molat or Olib - Ilovik - Lo</strong><strong>ṥinj  </strong>After breakfast and our morning swim, we sail to Ilovik, the 'Island of Flowers'. Then continue to Mali Lošinj, one of the most popular islands with its pine trees and clear waters. Overnight.</p>
<p><strong>Thursday  Lo</strong><strong>ṥinj - Cres </strong> We leave for the island of Cres. Mali Losinj and Cres used to be one island but a channel dug by the Romans now separates them. Overnight Cres.</p>
<p><strong>Friday  Cres - Opatija </strong> Your last day on board as we cruise back towards Opatija where we arrive late afternoon. Overnight Opatija.</p>
<p><strong>Saturday  Opatija </strong> After breakfast disembark for the transfer to Ljubljana airport and your flight home.</p>
</div>
<div> </div>
<div class="white_box_shadow">
<h2>What’s included</h2>
<ul>
<li><strong>Return flights to Ljubljana </strong>from Stansted &amp; Manchester</li>
<li><strong>Return airport transfers</strong></li>
<li><strong>3 nights half board </strong>at 4 Star Hotel Agava or 4 Star Hotel Grand in Opatija</li>
<li><strong>7 nights on board Ms. Dalmatia. </strong>Continental breakfast and lunch (with one drink) included.</li>
<li><strong>Sightseeing in Zadar</strong></li>
</ul>
<p> Tourist tax &amp; port fees (allow €20 per person per week) are not included and are payable locally. </p>
<div style="columns: 100px 2; -webkit-columns: 100px 2; /* safari and chrome */-moz-columns: 100px 2;"></div>
</div>
